description: The origin of Revenant begins here. Mike is a 13 year old kid who's had some rough times. His mother died giving birth to his younger sibling, he's just starting high school and he has just come to terms with more turmoil-- he's gay, and bullies have begun to attack him. But what hidden power does he possess, and what new hell is life going to put him through?
name: You Only Die Once

description:
Welcome to Flattown, Part 1

In the World of Entertainment, cartoons are real.

Once upon a time, classically drawn characters were cinematic royalty, and audiences loved them. Then the world changed. A fellow created a thing called a computer, and, almost without warning, it was the CGs that were selling out shows. Flat toons couldn’t get work, and the old stars were simply forgotten.

Enter RoboChuck. Made on a computer but raised by Flats, he is unwittingly the most important toon in the world. Too bad he’s stuck doing low budget TV commercials for a living.
name: Welcome to Flattown, Part 1

description: NON-HUMANS co-creator and co-writer NOAH DORSEY brings his second on-going comic series to life with the unique style of Hungarian illustrator ZSOMBOR HUSZKA. In this raw gothic noir the suicidal Simon Monroe recruits a psychopath called Honeycomb to kill him in four days. In those last days Simon decides to do a little good by helping people in dangerous situations. Saint Chaos is born. When Simon discovers that he may be able to uncover who had murdered his mother he needs the time to find her killer, but Honeycomb is hellbent on taking his life.

In the debut issue of "Simon Says", we get a peek at the daily life of Simon Williams in 1996...finishing up his high school year with his buds Nathan, Eddie, and Marvin, attempting to finally get his dream girl Morgan to notice him, and talking music and life with his new friend Angela. But, in less than a week, buzz worthy alternative band Kiki's Apron will be playing a sold out show in Simon's town. Can he score tickets to the show that everyone is talking about?

The vile Khn'Trra observes the planet Earth, strategizing a means of attack as she ponders on the origins of the principal members of the Sinsationals who she sees as an obstacle in her path for world domination.

This issue details the beginnings of each of the main characters.

person_credits.name: Scott Jones
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, letterer, cover, other

description:
What do you do when your whole world turns upside down?

Dana is a woman who doesn't deal well with confrontation. She likes her job, her friends, and the cozy comfort of her neighbourhood -- Toronto's own Queen Street West. But when the world forces her to stand up, will she be able to handle it?

SNOW is a unique graphic novel entirely set in Toronto's Queen Street West neighbourhood. It was nominated for a 2010 Gene Day Award and was awarded a Xeric Foundation grant in 2011.
name: GN

description: South Africa, 1879. The camp is surrounded by low, parched hills slowly rising to the mountain of Isandlwana, under which we are camped. Apparently we aren't the only ones who get up early and armed. There's a Zulu warrior, with whom we are officially not at war, looking at us from the ridge of the hill. He looks an awful lot like a scout.

Between illusion and truth, fear and hope, death and rebirth...In a war-ravaged land, the Russian president's sixteen-year-old daughter is kidnapped by a Georgian soldier. Thus begins a time-traveling, dark fantasy adventure about a pair of star-crossed lovers who uncover the deepest truth ever known. CHAPTER ONE: A DANGEROUS GAME, is the beginning of a twelve-issue, epic graphic novel.
name: Chapter One: A Dangerous Game

description:
This is the premiere issue of "Subject to Change", and we're pulling out all the stops!!

What is Kelly's secret? And what does it have to do with Divine Authority's ever-enigmatic heroine known simply as "-Girl!"? Carla will get the answers she's been looking for, but it's nothing she could have expected!! Meanwhile, Nightside gets to meet his superhero idol, Hotshot, who proves to be more than just an inspiration to him. This makes Metaphormer jealous, though not as a lovers' quarrel... he is jealous that Nightside considers him to be at the bottom of the "superhero totem pole" by comparison! And of course, it was never in doubt that he would place Icebox near the top...

This issue is a *Fun* introduction to our Unique cast of Characters!!

Shane Cook is dead. Sure, he may have been a drinker, a gambler, even an occasional petty crook, but Shane was not a bad guy. The question of "Who killed Shane Cook?" is less difficult to answer than the question, "Who didn't kill Shane Cooke?"

Magic Torch presents a terrifying selection of stories adapted from and inspired by Inverclyde folklore and legends.

Within, are cursed treasure maps, serpent worshipping cultists, trolls, ghosts, undead pirates and graverobbers in tales told by some of our most infamous horrors - Captain Kidd, Granny Kempock and Auld Dunrod.

Dare you shine a flickering candle on the darker corners of our local folklore?

Tart Acid wakes up in New York City circa the mid 1950's. She doesn't know where, or what year it is, but she knows this: Somewhere near her there's a demon wreaking havoc on the history of the world.

She must find it and stop it, or risk the world we live in being irrevocably changed.
What really divides America? Can we overcome our differences if we have to? What would happen if Red States and Blue States HAD to work together to survive.

Vicious barbarian Blood Billin finds himself stranded on a tropical island after a horrific shipwreck. Just as he finds new freedom from his deceased nautical jailers he discovers a new land full of dangers set on testing him. Through three confrontations with inhabitants on the island, Blood is forced to look inward and rethink his life of anarchy. A story of identity, redemption, and purpose.

person_credits.name: Mike Lariccia
person_credits.role: writer, artist, letterer, colorist, cover, other

volume.name: Too Fast: The Story of Blood Billin

description: Our heroes begin a journey but not to where they planned...

Whether he's napping, stealing cookies or chasing clones Yum Yum Chocobuns gives it his best! Hunger follows him wherever he goes but so does trouble. Fun is always on the menu as his greedy gut leads him to his next adventure. Time for Sweet Treats!

The Superior Spider-Man vs. The Amazing Spider-Man! Otto Octavius wants to eradicate the last remnants of Peter Parker from his mind once and for all!

By Dan Slott and Ryan Stegman.

Also: The Superior Spider-Man battles the new Mysterio and the Punisher!

By Christopher Yost and Davis Lopez.

Plus: Minimum Carnage begins! Carnage is back! And only Scarlet Spider and Agent Venom can stop him.

By Cullen Bunn, Christopher Yost and Lan Medina.

Includes material reprinted from: Superior Spider-Man #9, Avenging Spider-Man #22 and Minimum Carnage: Alpha #1.
Translates : A+X (2013) #06-11

The Good, The Bad, and the Demonic!

John Parker had it all. A decorated sharpshooter in the Civil War, he had a promising career ahead of him, a beautiful wife, and a newborn son. But after becoming embroiled in a dark and demonic conspiracy engineered by the Bakerton Detective Agency, he lost everything.

Fleeing to the West, a broken man, Parker reinvents himself as "No Man," a heartless gun-for-hire whose only solace comes from hunting and killing the demons who he helped set loose. With Buntline Special in hand, a deadly revolver with a 16 inch barrel, he blasts his way through a different kind of Old West, where strange and evil beings lurk.

NO MAN'S LAND: Not your father's cowboy tale.

Chapter One - Six.
name: Vol. 1

description:
John Parker is the "No Man," a heartless gun for hire who hunts demons in the Old West. But is he as heartless as he appears, and how did a young man reared in the Quaker ways transform into a cold-blooded killing machine?

The notorious Bakerton Detective Agency wants something that Parker took from them, the severed half of an ancient book called the Necronomicon. And they'll stop at nothing to get it back.

As his partner Cherokee Bill lies dying in the dust, Parker faces off against his arch nemesis, Doyle Bakerton, in the duel of a lifetime.

Haunted by demons both real and imagined, the truth finally emerges about Parker's tragic past...

Chapter Seven - Eleven.
name: Vol. 2

description: Stan Lee, the great innovator of the entertainment industry, teams up with BOOM! Studios to deliver a brand new line of superhero comics. In STARBORN, Stan Lee teams up with critically acclaimed writer Chris Roberson (iZOMBIE, CINDERELLA: FROM FABLETOWN WITH LOVE) and fan-favorite artist Khary Randolph (SPIDER-MAN, TEEN TITANS GO!) to present the story of a man not of this world! Benjamin Warner is a failed fantasy novelist, always dreaming of far off worlds and exciting adventures. But when a familiar face reenters his life, and devastating trouble follows, Benjamin learns his rejected stories weren't fiction but memories of his home planet! Benjamin's forgotten past comes crashing down around him as he finds himself at the center of a galactic war and is forced to face the truth that he is... not of this world!
name: Volume 1

description: In STARBORN, Stan Lee teams up with New York Times bestselling writer Chris Roberson (SUPERMAN, iZOMBIE, CINDERELLA: FROM FABLETOWN WITH LOVE) and fan-favorite artist Khary Randolph (SPIDER-MAN, TEEN TITANS GO!) to present the story of a man not of this world! Benjamin Warner is a failed fantasy novelist, always dreaming of far-off worlds and exciting adventures. But when a familiar face reenters his life, and devastating trouble follows, Benjamin learns his rejected stories weren't fiction but memories of his home planet! Benjamin's forgotten past comes crashing down around him as he finds himself at the center of a galactic war and is forced to face the truth that he is...not of this world! Volume 2 of the hit sci-fi superhero series.
name: Volume 2

description: Starborn sees Stan Lee join forces with New York Times bestselling writer Chris Roberson (Superman, iZombie, Cinderella: From Fabletown with Love) and world class artists Khary Randolph (Spider-Man, Teen Titans Go!) and Matteo Scalera (Deadpool) to present Volume 3 of the graphic novel series that is truly not of this world. A perfect jumping-on point for new readers, this collection sees Benjamin Warner fight to accept his unforgivable past as he takes up the unbelievable mantle of Starborn. With new menacing villains and other familiar superheroes, this graphic novel volume continues to be the most scintillating sci-fi superhero epic on the shelves.
name: Volume 3

description:
** Previously available only at Comic-Con International: San Diego 2013! **

Contains a brief interview by Alyssa Milano and Concept art by Marcus To & Ian Herring

WHY WE LOVE IT: From the creative mind of Alyssa Milano, with artist Marcus To (Huntress, Red Robin), and writers Jackson Lanzing and Collin Kelly, Hacktivist is a fast-paced cyber-thriller about friendship and freedom in a time war.

WHY YOU WILL LOVE IT: Fantastic characters and stunning action set pieces, beautifully illustrated by Marcus To (Cyborg 009, Red Robin) and Eisner-nominated colorist Ian Herring (Jim Henson's Tale of Sand).

WHAT IT’S ABOUT: Ed Hiccox and Nate Graft are young, brilliant, and the co-founders of YourLife, a social networking company that has changed the way the world stays connected. In secret, these best friends are also “sve_Urs3lf,” the largest, white-hat hacking group on the planet, exposing information and sparking revolutions across the globe.

In this volume, Astro Boy: The Faceless Robot concludes! Damdamís head is finally recovered and in Astro Boy's hands! Elsewhere, Dr. Maxun of the California State Robot Hospital explains the horrifying reason Damdam should never reattach his head. The stakes grow higher as Damdam and Astro battle for the fate of the world! Who will be victorious? Also included are Buddha, Adolf, and Black Jack!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Faceless Robot Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Five: Enter Ananda
  • Adolf: Days of Infamy Chapter Four
  • Black Jack: The Old Man and the Tree
name: Vol. 73

description:
Ever wonder how Astro Boy evolved as a character over the years? In this issue of Weekly Astro Boy Magazine, Tezuka drops in to give readers a sneak peek into the changes Astro's undergone since his first appearance in 1951! Then, in Astro Boy: The Secret of the Egyptian Conspirators, the good professors entrust Astro Boy with a priceless artifact: Cleopatra's mysterious pendant! Egyptian conspirators have their eyes set on Astro Boy's precious cargoóbut for what purpose? Also included are Buddha, Ode to Kirihito, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Secret of The Egyptian Conspirators Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Five: Detective Pampas
  • Ode To Kirihito: Goldgotha Hill
  • Black Jack: Twice Dead
name: Vol. 74

person_credits.name: Evan Dorkin
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: PART 2: For years, the 10th Muse has fought a variety of evil in the name of justice, but she has never battled the media! If the future is written, the Muse is a dead woman and there is nothing the gods can do about it. In the bigger-than-life series finale, Emma Sonnet encounters her final destiny...but will it mean her death? This is a giant-sized 44-page roller coaster ride that will keep fans on the edge of their seat until the very last page!

Hi dittle dee dee, an actor's life for me... There's a heavy price to pay when bringing a character to life, some might even call it... a curse. Ask iconic sci fi actor Bill Mumy. The Illuminati... secret Nazi moon base... the Akashic Records... a ghost boy... all this and Row Bot too. "The Curse of the Mumy"... an original new series created and written by Bill Mumy. Read it or be sent to the cornfield.

In the near future, three teens find themselves thrust into a twisted version of the Olympic Games against a horde of vicious sportsmen and a bloodthirsty crowd of spectators! David, Carrie, and Dean play a game where winning and losing are matters of life and death, from Ain't It Cool News' Mark L. Miller! In this special edition find new images and info that have never been seen before!
name: GN

description: Bluewater Productions is known for having developed some of the iconic female characters in independent comic books such as the 10th Muse, Legend of Isis and Judo Girl. This brand new graphic novel features not only Isis but some of the other Bluewater classic characters such as Venus, Valkyrie, Victoria's Secret Service, Gearz and Black Scorpion. Together for the 1st time in over 100 pages!
name: Volume 1

description: “Off with their head!” This phrase has echoed through history as the driving force behind one of the most memorable villains in all literature. But who is the Queen of Hearts really? The History of one of fantasies most iconic characters comes to life in this exciting new series from Bluewater Comics.

The whimsical, nonsensical stories exploring the fantasy world of Alice started with the simple friendship between young, beautiful Alice Liddell and the kind and creative Lewis Carroll. This books is a tribute to both the artistic use of the language displayed in the stories and the influence they have on modern literature, media, and art.

When a spontaneous time leap sends Nickolas Flux back to the Salem, Massachusetts, during the height of the witch trials, what's a teenage history buff to do? Try to avoid being tried for witchcraft, of course! From meeting accused witches to running from angry mobs, Nick must survive one of the most frightening moments in American history.
name: GN

volume.name: Arrested For Witchcraft!: Nickolas Flux and the Salem Witch Trials

description: When a spontaneous time leap sends Nickolas Flux back to the Battle of the Alamo, what's a teenage history buff to do? Join the ranks of the defenders, of course! From meeting Santa Anna to fighting alongside Davy Crockett, Nick must survive one of the most epic moments in Texas history.
name: GN

volume.name: Defend Until Death!: Nickolas Flux and the Battle of the Alamo

description: When a spontaneous time leap sends Nickolas Flux back to the Boston Tea Party, what's a teenage history buff to do? Join the rebellion, of course! From meeting Samuel Adams to dumping tea into Boston Harbor, Nick must survive one of the most pivotal moments in Colonial history.
name: GN

volume.name: Night of Rebellion!: Nickolas Flux and the Boston Tea Party

description: When a spontaneous time leap sends Nickolas Flux back to the California Gold Rush, what's a teenage history buff to do? Join the scramble to strike it rich, of course! From meeting John Sutter to panning for gold, Nick must survive one of the most pivotal events of American Westward Expansion.
name: GN

volume.name: Stake A Claim!: Nickolas Flux and the California Gold Rush

description: It's all-out action and excitement as the hit Disney XD TV show bursts off the screen and into your hands with four screen-capture adaptations from season one, including an episode scripted by Marvel scribe supreme Brian Michael Bendis! When Peter Parker discovers that Thor has been transformed into a Frog of Thunder, he must travel to Asgard to save the Nine Realms from Loki's wrath! Spider-Man teams up with X-Man Wolverine to take down the mutant Mesmero, but things get freaky when Mesmero switches the two heroes' personalities! Spidey's most dangerous foe, Venom, returns -and the sinister symbiote chooses Harry Osborn as its new host! An exhausted Spider-Man takes the weekend off, so of course that's when Dr. Octopus and the Whirlwind decide to strike! Collecting MARVEL UNIVERSE ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #17-20.
name: Volume 5

description: The Reavers have cooked up their deadliest cyborgs yet: Albert, a mechanical doppelganger of Wolverine, and his partner, the cute widdle Elsie-Dee! But that's just the start of the madness as Wolverine is targeted by mob enforcers, body-slammed by a stealth fighter, sucked into the sewers and savaged by Sabretooth - who somehow believes he's Wolverine's father! Jubilee, Forge, Cable and Nick Fury come to Wolverine's aid - but when the mythical Hunter in Darkness is captured and Lady Deathstrike arrives to take her revenge on Logan, it leads to a blood-soaked four-way claw fight in Times Square that can't possibly end well! Then, Wolverine and Wolfsbane are transported to a magical dimension to fulfill an ancient prophecy! Plus: a crazed zookeeper, an invisible demon and a vengeful sniper! Collecting WOLVERINE (1988) #38-46 and WOLVERINE: RAHNE OF TERRA.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Wolverine by Larry Hama and Marc Silvestri

description: Working for a secret subdivision of S.H.I.E.L.D., Hulk is sent on his most dangerous mission yet! After the events of AGE OF ULTRON, history is breaking - and only the Hulk is strong enough to hold it together - but only with Bruce Banner's help! It's Hulk vs. the Chronarchists in the last hours before the extinction of the dinosaurs! Kid Colt, Two-Gun Kid, Rawhide Kid and the Black Knight guest star - but when the Chronarchists arrive in the time of Camelot, can the Hulk triumph against Merlin the magician? As Bruce Banner finds himself literally running out of time, the Hulk returns to the present - but which Hulk? Answers had better come fast, because the final showdown with the Chronarchists looms - and it's time to smash! Collecting INDESTRUCTIBLE HULK #11-15.
name: Volume 3

description: Convicted of crimes he committed when he reverted to his Emperor Kurr persona, Dragon is locked up with the deadly villains he himself brought to justice. What follows isn't pretty. Collects SAVAGE DRAGON #187-192.
name: TPB

description: A young woman awakens in a hospital covered in scars as if she had been taken apart and put back together again. Her mind is as fragmented as her body, leaving her delusional and seeing monsters everywhere. Is this the work of a serial killer, or something far worse? FBI Agent Erin Scott intends to help her find out, with or without the approval of her superiors in this visionary modern, Mature re-imagining of the Frankenstein legend from acclaimed artist/creator Tyler Kirkham (New Guardians, Teen Titans, and Amazing Spider-Man).
name: TPB

description:
Relive the gripping, noir-esque launch of Peter David's most memorable concept: X-Factor Investigations! Jamie Madrox sets up shop in the heart of Mutant Town - but with so many duplicates out in the world, who is the real Madrox? Does he even know anymore? Then, when the fallout from the HOUSE OF M depowers most of the world's mutants, X-Factor must find answers - fast! With Guido, Wolfsbane, Siryn, M and Rictor by his side - as well as the stuff-knowing Layla Miller - Madrox must take on the manipulative prescient Mr. Tryp's rival group Singularity Investigations, navigate a superhuman Civil War, learn why the X-Men lied to his team, deal with the unbalanced Quicksilver's new ability to reboot mutant powers for a price and discover the deadly traitor in X-Factor's midst! Collecting MADROX #1-5 and X-FACTOR (2006) #1-12.

Collects Madrox #1-5 and X-Factor #1-12.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: X-Factor By Peter David: The Complete Collection

description:
The X-Men have just averted the Age of Apocalypse, but the threat of Onslaught looms right around the corner - a villain so powerful he put the unstoppable Juggernaut into a coma! But before the X-Men can learn more about this shadowy foe, they must face Gene Nation, led by the vicious Marrow - and help Magneto's Acolytes battle Apocalypse's son, Holocaust, who escaped the AoA into the Marvel Universe! Plus: How will the world react when the Legacy virus' existence is made public? Can Rogue handle learning Gambit's greatest secret? And did Sabretooth's brain damage truly change his personality, or is he a time bomb waiting to go off? All this, and the Xavier Institute enrolls a new student! Collecting X-MEN PRIME, UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #322-326, X-MEN (1991) #42-45 and ANNUAL '95, and X-MEN UNLIMITED (1993) #8.

Collects X-Men Prime, Uncanny X-Men #322-326, X-Men #42-45, X-Men Annual '95 andX-Men Unlimited #8.
name: Volume 1

description: Existential horror turns cosmic horror as something emerges from the shadows of the past, and it seems the team have one more thing to worry about. The Young Avengers race desperately across the multiverse in pursuit of their missing friend, but their road trip goes crazy as it reaches its destination. Because its destination is mainly excitement and heartbreak. Several Young Avengers decide what to do next - the question is, whether they decide to stay Young Avengers! Plus: Ever wonder what the super-hero equivalent of a terrible soul-sucking talent-wasting temp job is? Wonder what Tommy (a.k.a. Speed) has been up to? Wonder why mutant David Alleyne (a.k.a. Prodigy) hasn't been even in the background in any one of the eight thousand X-books? Discover answers herein! And hey, are you ready for Mother's Day? Collecting YOUNG AVENGERS (2013) #6-10.
name: Volume 2

person_credits.name: Charles M. Schulz
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: As the true nature of Brainiac’s plan begins to unfold, the League enlists the help of allies from across the globe…and beyond!
name: System Override Part 4 of 8: Overwrite
